<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <img src="http://placehold.it/300x300" alt="" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h1><%= @campaign.name %></h1>
    <% if @campaign.user == current_user %>
    <%= link_to "Edit", edit_campaign_path(@campaign), class:"btn btn-primary" %>
    <%= link_to "Delete", @campaign, method: :delete, class:"btn btn-danger"  %>
    <% end %>
    <h2><small class="text-muted"><%= @campaign.organization %></small></h2> #some developers deprecate tags like small and the like are essentially just styling. I'll use styling tags sometimes though so I'm not cluttering up my stylesheet with one-offs, though if you get into that spot, it makes sense to break up your styling into mutliple sheets
    <p>Ends in <%= distance_of_time_in_words(@campaign.end_date, Time.now)%> (<%= @campaign.end_date.strftime("%D") %>)</p>
    <% if @campaign.current_amount >= @campaign.goal_amount %>
      <progress class="progress progress-success" value="<%= @campaign.current_amount %>" max="<%= @campaign.goal_amount %>"></progress>
    <% else %>
      <progress class="progress progress-info" value="<%= @campaign.current_amount %>" max="<%= @campaign.goal_amount %>"></progress>
    <% end %>
    <p>$<%= number_with_precision(@campaign.current_amount, :precision => 2, :delimiter => ',') %> of $<%= number_with_precision(@campaign.goal_amount, :precision => 2, :delimiter => ',') %> raised </p> # you may want to off-load some of the logic on the beginning of this line for rails-style bonus points. generally, you want to keep your views as free of 'business logic' as much as possible. I think of the controller as a place where you are preparing the data for the view
    <p><%= link_to "Support", new_campaign_pledge_path(@campaign) %></p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row description">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <p class="lead">
      <%= @campaign.description %>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
